page.title: 03Houses at Manningtree
page.content: In the High Street the houses are fairly old. My house (no.48) is over 300 years old, you can tell by the structure of the beams in the loft. It has two fireplaces upstairs, which we think are Edwardian. The two houses beside us (no.46,44) are about the same age as ours. All of these three houses used to be one doctor's surgery and there is a door in one of our cupboards connecting to next door. After that it was a grocer's shop and you can see the lump where the sign was. There are also large windows like shop windows. By Elizabeth Cleveland, 12 years old.
